e 'Camino Real. This hike will start to acclimatise you to the high altitude, and is of a moderate level. You will be hiking for approximately six hours before arriving at the Salkantay Lodge. In the distance you will be able to see the glacier peak of Mount Salkantay. Settle into your room or make the most of the outdoor jacuzzi before enjoying dinner and a briefing of the next day ahead.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in lodges . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Mollepata mountain village stop</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>3</day1><day2>3</day2><destfrom>Lake Humantay</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will have another opportunity to acclimatize with a half-day hike to Lake Humantay. Ascend the slopes behind the lodge, hiking for an hour and a half before reaching the spectacular Humanity glacier. Lake Humanity will dazzle you with its stunning blue water and pristine landscapes. Relax at the lake and enjoy the tranquillity before hiking back to the lodge. After lunch the remainder of the day is at your leisure. Soak in the jacuzzi, treat yourself to a relaxing massage (at an extra cost) or sit back and enjoy your beautiful surroundings.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in lodges . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>4</day1><day2>4</day2><destfrom>Salkantay Pass &amp; Wayra Lodge</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This is the most challenging day yet as you trek in total for approximately six to eight hours. After an early start you will hike up the Rio Blanco Valley. You will ascend to the highest point on the Salkantay Pass which is 4,638 metres above sea level. Admire views of the the snow-capped peaks of the Vilcabamba Range and the glacier face of Mount Salkantay above, before descending  through giant mountain boulders. Tonight you can enjoy a well-earned rest at Wayra Lodge, our most remote lodge on the trek.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in lodges . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>5</day1><day2>5</day2><destfrom>Salkantay River &amp; Colpa Lodge</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>After a leisurely breakfast, descend along the banks of the Salkantay River into a cloud forest. Feel the warm air and spot colourful butterflies and beautiful orchids along the way. You will see some of the villagers as the hike takes you past their rural homes.  Arrive at Colpa Lodge where you can enjoy Pachamanca, a traditional Peruvian meal. It  is a tasty dish of seasoned meat baked in a earthen cooking pot. This afternoon you can do an optional bike ride to Collpapampa.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in lodges . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>6</day1><day2>6</day2><destfrom>Santa Teresa River Valley &amp; Lucma Lodge</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Hike through Santa Teresa valley, home to some of the more populated areas of this rural region. You will pass banana, granadilla and avocado orchards before stopping to enjoy a hot picnic lunch by the river. This afternoon you will tour a coffee plantation that produces some of the best organic coffee in the world. You will notice a shift in the climate, as the air becomes more tropical due to the proximity to the Amazon Jungle. Tonight you will stay at Lucma Lodge.</p><p>Instead of this trek you have the option to take a zip-line in Santa Teresa at an extra cost. It is one of the highest in South America comprising of seven cables over two vast jungle valleys. This is a full day activity and you will be transferred to Lucma Lodge later in the evening.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) i